## Review points

- Trivy can be used in the supply-chain workflow to review known vulnerabilities.
- Syft can be used to prepare an SBOM so dependencies are traceable.
- Cosign signing is optional and usually needs a registry-backed image reference.
- GitHub Actions security workflow generation can automate image build, scan preparation, SBOM preparation, and artifact upload.
- Prefer stable image tags or digests over mutable tags.

## Limits

This file does not run a scanner and does not claim that a scan has passed. It documents how to connect the local supply-chain readiness module and CI readiness module into a manual review process.
